Abstract

This study employs NLP techniques to extract keyword features from property advertisement texts and applies machine learning models to quantify the impacts of these keyword features on the housing price. This study extracts 25 keyword features most frequently mentioned, involving five aspects: property ownership, purchase chain, location characteristics, functional zonings, and some other housing attributes. Six among 25 keywords features: central heating, no chain, good location, double bedroom, garden orientation, and ground floor, are found to have a greater impact on housing prices than other keyword features. Except for the garden orientation, the other five housing characteristics have a negative impact on housing prices. Through further analysis, this paper speculates that the most common keyword features in property descriptions tend to be the marketing focus of cheap properties. This study contributes to enhancing the property dataset to improve current housing price prediction.

